<br>
In one of his books, can't recall the name right now, a scientist develops this kind of nanotechnology. He then proceeds to test it's capabilities by inventing a system of molecular mini-processors that through intravenous injections could assemble themselves inside a human body and allow perfect communication and manipulation for all of that persons cells (or something like that, read this like 9 years ago). He plans for it to somehow better the human race by making our bodies perfect in every sense with complete control...only he decides to remove all emotions except fear so that we don't start to destroy eachother.<br>
<br>
The effect heightens our levels of fear though, and people start de-evolving instead of evolving, into creatures and monsters and shit.<br>
<br>
Been a loooong time since I read that book, but try to hunt it down before you get all gung-ho about news like this.  Sure it's a fictional story all the way, but the way they're making advancements and with some of the people we've got out there...<br>
